DA leader Mmusi Maimane has suspended Helen Zille &#8211; he announced on Saturday.Maimane said the country lived in a &#8220;fragile democracy which means our public representatives must, at all times, be sensitive to the legitimate anger that people still feel about our past and its legacy.&#8221;It was important to rebuild public trust and he had asked &#8220;Ms Zille to tender an unreserved apology to both South Africa and the DA for the damage she has done. Unfortunately, she declined.&#8221;ZilleIn addition he said, Zille had continued to damage the party with various pieces of communication that seek to undermine what we are trying to achieve.It was with this in mind that the Federal Executive has resolved Ms Zille be suspended from all party related activities until such time as her disciplinary hearing is concluded, he said in a statement.She would be served with a notice.&#8220;This has not been an easy decision. But, as the Leader, I must do what is right for the party and South Africa,&#8217; Maimane said.&nbsp;